title: Teide
summary: Teide, or Mount Teide, (Spanish: El Teide, Pico del Teide, pronounced [ˈpiko ðel ˈtejðe], "Teide Peak") is a volcano on Tenerife in the Canary Islands, Spain. Its summit (at 3,715 m (12,188 ft))[1][lower-alpha 1] is the highest point in Spain and the highest point above sea level in the islands of the Atlantic.
